<div class="work-header">
  <h1 class="work-title">GPS Navigation Device</h1>
  
  <div class="work-description">
    Designing a distraction-free, dedicated hardware navigation tool for Swiggy and Zomato delivery partners to reduce cognitive load and improve safety.
  </div>

  <span class="work-meta">October 2025</span>
</div>

<div class="hero-container">
    <img src="https://picsum.photos/id/1/1200/600" alt="Final Prototype on a Bike Handlebar" class="hero-img">
</div>

<div class="case-study-body">

## The Challenge
Delivery partners often struggle with phone batteries dying and distractions from other apps (WhatsApp, Calls) while navigating. Constant notification pop-ups cover the map at critical turns.

**The Goal:** Build a device that does *one thing* perfectly—navigation.

## The Solution
I prototyped a hardware device using the **ESP32 WROOM** board and a 1.8-inch TFT display. The device connects to the user's phone via Bluetooth but filters out all noise.

![Wiring Diagram](https://picsum.photos/id/60/800/400)
<p class="caption">Initial wiring sketch and breadboard prototype</p>

It displays only the essentials:
* Direction Arrow (Turn Left/Right)
* Distance to turn (e.g., 200m)
* Street Name

## Outcomes
The prototype successfully reduced battery drain on the main smartphone by allowing the screen to remain off. Testers reported feeling "less anxious" about missing turns in traffic.

